HEADWORD: Lustrum
<hw>Lus"trum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> E.
<plw>Lustrums</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, L. <plw>Lustra</plw>
<pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. Cf. 2d & 3d <er>Luster</er>.]</ety> <def>A
lustration or purification, especially the purification of the whole
Roman people, which was made by the censors once in five years.</def>
<specif>Hence:</specif> <def>A period of five years.</def>⟦br⟧
